<!--Migrate Schema-->

After assessing your databases, the next step is to execute the schema migration process by using the Data Migration Assistant (DMA).

### Steps

To use DMA to create a migration project, perform the following steps.

1. Create a **New Migration** project

   a. Click on the New (+) icon, select the **Migration** project type, select **SQL Server** as the source and **Azure SQL Database** as the target, select **Schema only** as the Migration scope, and then select **Create**.

   ![New Migration](https://mpbdevcontent.azureedge.net/Images/dmamigrate.png)    

   b. Provide source SQL server conenction details, select **Connect**, select the database(s) that you want to assess, and then selct **Next**.

   ![Source Server details](https://mpbdevcontent.azureedge.net/Images/dmaazuredbconnecttosource.png)    

   c. Provide target Azure SQL Database conenction details. Click "Connect". Select a single database in Azure SQL Database target. Click "Next"
    
   ![Target Server details](https://mpbdevcontent.azureedge.net/Images/dmaazuredbconnecttotarget.png)    
    
   d. Select database schema objects from the source that you want migrated. Click "Generate SQL Script"
    
   ![Select Database Objects](https://mpbdevcontent.azureedge.net/Images/dmaazuredbgeneratescript.png)    
    
   e. Script is generated and they can be edited in the textarea before deployment. If no edits are required, click "Deploy Schema"
    
   ![Deploy Schema](https://mpbdevcontent.azureedge.net/Images/dmaazuredbdeployschema.png)  
    
   **Note**: Review the right pane for deployment status. Update the deployment script(s) for failures and attempt re-deploying schema.
    
   f. After schema deployment is successful, select **Migrate Data". Select tables containing data you want migrated
    
   ![Data Migration](https://mpbdevcontent.azureedge.net/Images/dmaazuredbselecttables.png)  
    
   **Note**: For data migration, only one database can be moved at a given time. Repeat the steps above for subsequent database migration
    
   g. Select **Start data migration**. 
    
   h. Review Migration Results when the process is complete.
    
    ![Data Migration](https://mpbdevcontent.azureedge.net/Images/dmaazuredbmigratedata.png)  
    
